Chickpea (chicken) Soup
  --Joy Manning
  
1/4 c olive oil
2 onions, chopped
3 stalks celery, chopped
1 carrot, chopped
6 cloves garlic, chopped
1 tsp salt
1 tsp dried dill
1/2 tsp ground black pepper
1/2 tsp turmeric
3 c cooked chickpeas (or 2x15 oz cans, drained)
8 c water
1/4 c nutritional yeast
1 c green peas (thawed if frozen) 

Warm the olive oil in a large soup pot over medium heat. Add the onions, celery, and carrot and cook until softened, ~8-10 min. Add the garlic, salt, dill, black pepper, and turmeric and cook until fragrant, ~1 min more. Add the chickpeas, water, and nutritional yeast and bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook on low, partially covered, for 30 min. Off heat, add the green peas. 


Notes: can sub veggie stock for the water, skip the nooch; can stir in sooked pasta prior to serving to make it chickpea noodle soup

